author: @padresilviorobertomic
content: “It was free “. Really? The city of Rio de Janeiro paid more than $10 million for this show and the State of Rio $10 million more. The total =  $20 million from the state plus the embezzlement that always happens in things like that here. You foreigners have no idea how public money is used in Brazil, while people are in poverty and in trouble all the time due to the lack of infrastructure. We are talking about a country that is struggling with poverty and corruption and, at this very moment, completely under water in some parts of it. That’s an absurd!
